                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#72ra" n="#6">Fol. 72ra, l.6</locus>: Scribe´s note on completing the work.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 72ra, l.6: ተፈጸመ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ አሥልጢ፡ ዘወንጌለ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ዘጳውሎስ፡ ወሐዋርያ፡ ወግብር፡ በፈቃደ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአጽሐፋ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ምኅጽንተ፡ ማርያም፡ በወርቁ፡ ለመቅደሰ፡ ሰማዝ፡ ወጸሐፊሃኒ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞሙ፡ ኀበ፡ አምደ፡ ወርቅ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን። </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The title of the work, Mäṣḥafä ʾaślǝṭi, is mentioned. The names of the commissioner, priest (qäsis) Mǝḫṣǝntä Maryam, and of the scribe, Zä-Wäldä Maryam, are also mentioned.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#72rb">Fol. 72rb</locus>: Note on the benefactors of the church.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 72rb: ዘሐነጻ፡ ለመቅደሰ፡ ሰማዝ፡ አቡነ፡ ዓጽፈ፡ ድንግል፡ በ፫፡ አምደ፡ እብን። ወዘተከላ፡ ወይነ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ተክለ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወዘአጽሐፋ፡ ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ምኅፅንተ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘሠረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ወዘተአደዋ፡ ፍሑቀ፡ ይኩን፡ እሱረ፡ ወውጉዛ፡ ይኩን፡ በቃለ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ኢትርስዑነ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the same hand as the main text. The note mentions the name of the builder of the church ʾabunä ʿAṣfä Dǝngǝl, the one who planted the grapevine priest (qäsis) Täklä Krǝstos, and the commissioner of the Ms. qäsis Mǝḫṣǝntä Maryam.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#72rb" n="#11">Fol. 72rb, l.11-72</locus>va: Note on commemoration days of some saints and individuals.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the same hand as Additio 1. The note mentions both Ethiopian and non-Ethiopian saints, and also two benefectors referred to in Addition 2 (Täklä Krǝstos, ʿAṣfä Dǝngǝl).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#72ra" n="#16">Fol. 72ra, l.16</locus>: Record concerning a donation of clothes made by Sǝbḥat ʾAragawi (ca. 1844-1914), governor of ʿAgamä.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 72ra, l.16: ዛቲ፡ ፬አልባስ፡ ዘወሀቦሙ፡ ለጻድቃን፡ ዘሰማዝ፡ ሹም፡ አጋሜ፡ ስብሐት። ፩፩፡ ኢትርስኡኒ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Directives for the ministers are written in the margins in the same hand as the main text: fols. 26rb, 27ra, 27rb, 27vb, 28va, 29rb, 29vb, 30rb, 30vb, 31rb, 31vb, 32rb, 33ra, 33rb, 33va, 33vb.&#xD;
- Crude note in pen: fols. 8va.</item>
